reviewText: I\This is my favorite gospel group, they get better with age love em!, ,I am more than happy with the  DVd
5 Stars! Love the group with their tight violin sound. This is a must purchase, go get it if you don't have it already.
My mom loves quartets.  This DVD definitely fits the bill.  She watches it twice a day.  Very clear and good quality.

I enjoyed the DVD very much, I wish that it was longer and contained newer tunes in addition to the old ones. The production quality was great, the lighting and sound was well done. Also the quality of the perfomance was superb. I am a long time fan of the Fantastic Violinairs and I was please to know that they released a new project, especially a live presentation. I was also happy to know that they consolidated the two exiting groups which gives us the best of the current violinaires. I would recomend it to any Violinaire fan, but don't expect an extended perfomance it right at an hour long which is still pretty good.

I really enjoyed this video. It is very inspirational. It brings back soooo many memories when Robert Blair was the leader. It is wonderful that Danny and Robert (members when Robert Blair was the leader) brought that wonderful harmony to this group. That harmony was really Fantastic.
A GROUP THAT SEEM AS THOUGH LONG FORGOTTEN SURFACED TO PRODUCE THE MUSIC AND MESSAGES IN SONGS THAT ARE HEART WARMING AND INSPIRATIONAL.
Very good purchase.  Good gospel singing.
not the best performance. thought they were going to sing more of the classics
Bought as a gift, recipient was happy
I am old school love the CD
Sorry fellas there was only one Robert Blair. But, you guys do a commendable job of keeping the idea of the Fantastic Violinaires going. For that you get the 4th star.

I purchased the DVD and CD, I am a fan of the orginal Violinares. They are true quartet sounds. Lil Blair sounds much like the deceased leader Robert Blair. They are to be commend for staying true to the sounds of the Violinares. Enjoyed all songs.
